cart.name: 2x2 Pyraminx
cart.description: While this puzzle is possible to "scramble", you will find that there are only three moving parts and should be able to solve it very easilly! Still a great addition for collectors!

cart.name: 5x5 Pyraminx
cart.description: The largest pyramidal puzzle in existence today, this puzzle requires serious discipline to master. Notice the curved shape, it must be designed that way to accommodate all the pieces!

cart.name: 1x1 Cube
cart.description: The smallest and most trivial of the cubic puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

cart.name: 5x5 Pyraminx
cart.description: The largest pyramidal puzzle in existence today, this puzzle requires serious discipline to master. Notice the curved shape, it must be designed that way to accommodate all the pieces!

cart.name: 4x4 Pyraminx
cart.description: The next higher order puzzle from the traditional Pyraminx. Good luck with this one.

cart.name: Original Pyraminx (3x3 Pyraminx)
cart.description: The traditional Pyraminx puzzle. It turns on its 4 exes stemming inwards from each tip of the puzzle. Watch as the pieces get quickly mixed up and try to put them back!

cart.name: 2x2 Cube
cart.description: Some mistake this as an easy puzzle since it's smaller than the traditional Rubik's cube. While they are correct that it has less pieces, they will find themselves lost if they try to unscramble it!

cart.name: 1x1 Pyraminx
cart.description: The smallest and most trivial of the pyramidal puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

cart.name: 11x11 Cube
cart.description: This cube is so large that its predecessor (the 10x10 cube) can't even be built because it lacks the necessary structure found in odd-numbered cubes. It has 726 stickers! Good luck!

cart.name: Monominx (1x1 Megaminx)
cart.description: The smallest and most trivial of the dodecahedral puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

cart.name: Monominx (1x1 Megaminx)
cart.description: The smallest and most trivial of the dodecahedral puzzles. Comes pre-solved!

cart.name: 6x6 Cube
cart.description: At three orders of magnitude larger than the original Rubik's Cube, this cube has 216 stickers.
